From: Wayne Hogrefe <whogrefe@focusanswers.com> [edited

A comment on Dr. Michael Sauri's personal observations regarding immunity
to smallpox (see: Part [3 of Smallpox, re-vaccination & immunity
20011029.2672
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Of huge importance in Dr. Sauri's response is what does he mean by "...only
a handful of immune responses were noted..."?
The main question we are faced with is how do we define "immune response"
and more importantly "protective immune responses" short of in vivo challenges?
--
Wayne Hogrefe
Focus Technologies
<whogrefe@focusanswers.com>
